Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for seven and one-half (7.5) years on count 1 and three (3) years on count 3.
Conditions of probation:
1) Pay restitution of $28,964.61 to Selective Insurance (Troullier claim), in a monthly amount to be determined by the agent;
2) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process and at the agents discretion;
3) Maintain fulltime employment or work search;
4) AODA assessment and follow through, at the agents discretion;
5) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same, at the agents discretion;
6) Maintain absolute sobriety;
7) Have no contact with Craig Troullier and Tobin Hynek or their property;
8) Pay court costs;
9) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
10) spend five (5) months in the county jail, under the Huber Law, on count 1 only, commencing on 09-01-17 at 6:00 p.m.  Court authorizes transfer to Kewaunee County Jail and further authorizes travel time of one hour per day, to be excluded, when calculating Huber release.
Minutes.
